## Detailed Comparison

| Feature | Squarespace | Relume (+ Webflow) | Winner |
|---------|-------------|-------------------|--------|
| **Speed to Launch** | 2-4 hours | 4-8 hours | Squarespace |
| **Design Freedom** | Medium (templates) | High (components) | Relume |
| **Learning Curve** | Low | Medium-High | Squarespace |
| **E-commerce** | Built-in excellent | Requires Webflow Ecommerce | Squarespace |
| **Custom Code** | No access | Full access | Relume |
| **Template Library** | 150+ templates | AI-generated components | Tie |
| **Monthly Cost** | $23-65 | $0 (Relume) + $23-224 (Webflow) | Squarespace |
| **Code Export** | No | Yes (Webflow) | Relume |

## What Is Relume?

**Relume** is an AI-powered component library that integrates with Webflow. It generates website sections and pages using AI, which you can then customize in Webflow.

**Key Points:**
- Relume is FREE to use
- You pay for Webflow subscription
- Requires Webflow knowledge
- Best for designers/developers

## Bottom Line

**For most users:** Squarespace wins on ease and speed
**For Webflow users:** Relume adds powerful AI capabilities
**For complete beginners:** Squarespace is the clear choice

